\b7NAME\c9
\tlibvt - abstraction layer useful in interfacing with the terminal

\b7DESCRIPTION\c9
\tThe \b7libvt\c9 library is a small utility library providing some simple abstractions over the raw VT100 terminal.  It provides facilities to set and get the cursor position as well as screen size.

\tIf the input or output device is not a terminal, no error will be raised but the cursor will not be moved and the returned resolution will be (\b51\c9, \b51\c9).

\b7FUNCTIONS
\t\b2libvt.setCursor\b4(\b7x\c9:\b5number\c9, \b7y\c9:\b5number\b4)\c9
\t\tMoves the terminal cursor to the specified X and Y coordinates.  Equivalent to \b2io.write\b4(\b3"\\27\b3[\b5YY\b3;\b5XX\b3H"\b4)\c9.

\t\b2libvt.getCursor\b4()\c9: \b5number\c9, \b5number\c9
\t\tReturns the current cursor position, or \b51\c9, \b51\c9 if the current input or output device is not a TTY.

\t\b3libvt.getResolution\b4(): \b5number\c9, \b5number\c9
\t\tReturns the current screen resolution, or \b51\c9, \b51\c9 if the current input or output device is not a TTY.

